<div class="question-card" id="card-78" data-qid="78" data-type="single">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 79</span>
    <span class="q-tag single">Single Choice</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      What service is provided by POP3?
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-78">
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Uses encryption to provide secure remote access to network devices and servers.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Retrieves email from the server by downloading the email to the local mail application of the client.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Allows remote access to network devices and servers.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">An application that allows real-time chatting among remote users.</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-78" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-78">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-78"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        The service provided by POP3 (Post office Protocol version 3) is:
        <br><br>
        <strong>Retrieves email from the server by downloading the email to the local mail application of the client.</strong>
        <br><br>
        POP3 is an email retrieval protocol that is used to download emails from a remote server to a local client. This allows users to access their emails while offline, as they are stored on their device after download.
      </div>
    </div>
